# ASKILL Project Context

Enterprise landing page for ASKILL S.A.S (industrial automation and control). Migrating from Webpack + vanilla JS to Next.js 16 App Router.

## Stack

- Package manager: pnpm (never npm or yarn)
- Framework: Next.js 16, React 19, TypeScript
- Styling: Tailwind CSS v4 via `@tailwindcss/postcss`
- Linting: ESLint flat config with `eslint-config-next`

## Project Structure

- `app/` — Next.js App Router (new UI lives here)
- `components/` — React components (create as needed during migration)
- `src/` — Legacy vanilla JS/CSS (reference only; do not modify unless explicitly requested)
- `public/` — Static assets served by Next.js

## Design Tokens (Tailwind v4)

Defined in `app/globals.css`:

- `askill-black`: #1c1c1c
- `askill-orange`: #ee752f
- Fonts: Ubuntu (primary), Montserrat, DynaPuff, Roboto, Rowdies via `next/font/google`

## Migration Guidelines

- Migrate UI section by section as atomic conventional commits (e.g., `feat(ui): migrate header`)
- Preserve existing copy, class semantics, and interaction behavior from legacy code
- Use Tailwind utilities with mobile-first responsive design (`sm:`, `md:`, `lg:`, `xl:`)
- Prefer `next/image` for images and `next/link` for navigation
- Extract client interactivity into `'use client'` components only when needed
- Keep commits focused: config changes separate from UI migration

## Commands

```bash
pnpm dev    # development server
pnpm build  # production build
pnpm lint   # ESLint
```
